Grip each almond between your thumb and index finger and pinch. The almond should slide right out of its skin. You can prevent the almond from flying across the room by using your opposite hand to form a shield and catch the slippery little almond! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d4/Blanch-Almonds-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Blanch-Almonds-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d4/Blanch-Almonds-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Blanch-Almonds-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
